Feature importance in random forest

Source: R/multivariate.R
importance_rf.Rd

Extracts feature importance in random forest in a nice format.

Usage

importance_rf(rf)

Arguments

rf

An object of class randomForest

Value

A data frame of feature importance.

See also

randomForest, fit_rf

Examples

data(example_set)
rf <- fit_rf(example_set, y = "Group")
rf
#> 
#> Call:
#>  randomForest(x = x, y = colData(object)[, y], importance = importance) 
#>                Type of random forest: classification
#>                      Number of trees: 500
#> No. of variables tried at each split: 8
#> 
#>         OOB estimate of  error rate: 48%
#> Confusion matrix:
#>     A B QC class.error
#> A  15 5  0        0.25
#> B  11 9  0        0.55
#> QC  4 4  2        0.80
importance_rf(rf)
